(63, 'Frequently asked questions', '<h4>\n	1- Who can be the supervisor a doctoral thesis?</h4>\n<p>\n	The appointment of the director may fall on any Spanish or foreign doctor, with proven research experience, regardless of the university, the center or the institution in which it provides services.</p>\n<h4>\n	2- How many supervisors can a thesis have?</h4>\n<p>\n	A doctoral thesis can be supervised by 3 doctors at the most.</p>\n<h4>\n	3- How many doctoral theses can a doctor supervise?</h4>\n<p>\n	A doctor can supervise five doctoral theses simultaneously at the most.</p>\n<h4>\n	4- Who can be the tutor of your doctoral thesis?</h4>\n<p>\n	The tutor of your thesis must always be a professor of the Department of Surgery or the Department of Morphological Sciences of UAB.</p>\n<h4>\n	5- How long does the PhD in Surgery and Morphological Sciences last?</h4>\n<p>\n	The duration of doctoral studies will depend on your dedication.</p>\n<p>\n	The full-time dedication lasts for at least two years and maximum three years from the admission date to the doctoral program. The part-time dedication lasts for at least four years and maximum five years from the admission date to the doctoral program.</p>\n<p>\n	The dedication regime is informed when presenting your research project, when formalizing the enrolment and in the commitment document and it is approved in the research plan, by which thing, any variation in this aspect must follow the procedure established for its modification.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', 104, '', 4, 2),
