(74, 'Frequently asked questions', '<h4>\n	1- What&nbsp; documentation do I need to bring with the registration form for first year registration?</h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		If you have a Spanish university degree and a Masters degree or PhD from the UAB:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Photocopy of ID document (DNI/NIE or passport).</li>\n			<li>\n				Passport-sized photo.</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		If you have a Spanish university degree and a Masters degree or PhD from another Spanish university:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Attested copy of your degree certificate and Masters degree certificate.</li>\n			<li>\n				Academic certificates or attested photocopies of the records of your degree and Masters degree.</li>\n			<li>\n				Photocopy of ID document(DNI/NIE or passport).</li>\n			<li>\n				Two passport-sized photographs.</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		If your degree is not from a Spanish university:\n		<ul>\n			<li>\n				Attested photocopies of your degree (or equivalent) and Masters degree. These should be legalized for countries outside the EU. Certificates issued in languages other than Catalan, Spanish or English must be translated in accordance with the official translation guidelines which you can find in the Legalizations section of this website.</li>\n			<li>\n				Academic certificates or attested photocopies of your degree (or equivalent) and Masters degree. These should be legalized for countries outside the EU. Certificates issued in languages other than Catalan, Spanish or English must be translated in accordance with the official translation guidelines which you can find in the Legalizations section of this website.</li>\n			<li>\n				Photocopy of ID document(DNI/NIE or passport).</li>\n			<li>\n				Two passport-sized photographs.</li>\n		</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>\n	2- How can I enroll online?</h4>\n<p>\n	You can self-register using the following link: <a href="http://sia.uab.es/servei/ALU_AUMDOC_PORT_ENG.html" target="_blank">PhD online enrolment</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	You can create a User and a Password in this <a href="http://sia.uab.es/cgi-bin/gpwd/gestio_pwd.html?&amp;idioma=en&amp;pais=GB" target="_blank">link</a>.</p>\n<p>\n	If you could not get your password or NIU from the web service SIA, you can send an email to the address <a href="mailto:ep.admissions@uab.cat">ep.admissions@uab.cat</a> or can call the School of Doctoral Studies at +34 93 5813836. If you work at a university hospital of the UAB, you can also go to apply for your password and NIU to the academic secretary of its Teaching Unit of the Faculty of Medicine.</p>\n<h4>\n	3- What fields should I fill in the statement of commitment?</h4>\n<p>\n	In section 3 of the statement of commitment you have to choose if you are going to do the PhD with full-time dedication or part-time dedication.</p>\n<p>\n	The statement of commitment must be signed by all supervisors and the tutor.<br />\n	In section Annex you should fill at least the number and frequency of the meetings you will have with your supervisors.</p>\n<h4>\n	4- What fields should I fill in the activities document?</h4>\n<p>\n	You should only fill the service of the hospital where you commit to attend and participate actively in the training sessions that are carried out periodically, and if you are interested in doing another optative activity. This document must be signed by the PhD student.</p>\n<h4>\n	5- Is it mandatory to tick optative activities?</h4>\n<p>\n	No, our PhD programme only demands to fulfill the 2 mandatory activities. But if you tick one optative activities you will have to upload its certificate to the web service SIA.</p>\n<h4>\n	6- What fields should I fill in the research plan?</h4>\n<p>\n	You should fill your personal data, your signature, supervisor&rsquo;s name and surname/s and tutor&rsquo;s name and surname/s.</p>\n<p>\n	The research plan will be sent filled with your data by the secretary of the programme.<br />\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', 105, '', 3, 2),
